The paper deals with parallel computation and graph algorithms, which are typically covered in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories of arXiv CS. Given that the paper focuses on the Massively Parallel Computation (MPC) model and graph problems, cs.DC and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves degree reduction techniques, which are relevant to cs.CC and cs.DM. Finally, the paper's focus on improving the efficiency of algorithms suggests that it could also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
